name: CI/CD Pipeline

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - staging
      - main

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
    - name: Checkout Code
      uses: actions/checkout@v3

    - name: Setup Python
      uses: actions/setup-python@v4
      with:
        python-version: 3.10

    - name: Install Dependencies
      run: |
        pip install -r requirements.txt

    - name: Run Migrations
      run: |
        python manage.py migrate

    - name: Collect Static Files
      run: |
        python manage.py collectstatic --noinput

    - name: Deploy to EC2
      run: |
        echo "${{ secrets.SSH_KEY }}" > key.pem
        chmod 600 key.pem
        ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -i key.pem ubuntu@YOUR_EC2_IP << 'EOF'
          cd /home/ubuntu/app
          git pull origin main
          source venv/bin/activate
          pip install -r requirements.txt
          python manage.py migrate
          python manage.py collectstatic --noinput
          sudo systemctl restart gunicorn
          sudo systemctl restart nginx
        EOF


-The pipeline is triggered on push to staging and main branches. It installs dependencies, runs migrations, collects static files, and deploys to EC2 using SSH.

Store in GitHub Secrets:
SSH private key
EC2 IP
DB credentials


1. Docker 
I would containerize the application using Docker.
Why?
-Same environment everywhere
-Easier deployment
-No “works on my machine” issues

2. Terraform (Infra as Code)
I would use Terraform to automate AWS infrastructure.
Why?
-Reproducible infra
-Version-controlled
-No manual EC2 setup

